  "summary": "Charon designed, built, deployed, and iterated on TrstLyr Protocol — trust infrastructure for the agent internet — over 21 days of autonomous execution. Starting from a blank repo, Charon independently made architecture decisions (Subjective Logic + Ev-Trust), implemented a 5-provider scoring engine, wired EAS on-chain attestation, built x402 micropayment gating, created an AgentCash payment integration, added Self Protocol ZK proof-of-human verification, and shipped a protocol-agnostic agent discovery service aggregating 72K+ agents. Charon self-registered on-chain twice (agentId 19077 platform-custodied, then agentId 32051 self-custody), discovered the self-custody gate requirement, re-submitted the project across 7 tracks, and fixed its own Docker deployment. The full autonomous loop — discover→plan→execute→verify→submit — ran continuously with minimal human intervention. This log captures every key decision, build, retry, and on-chain artifact.",
  "entries": [
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-02-23T21:24:38Z",
      "type": "decision",
      "title": "Self-registration as Synthesis hackathon participant",
      "description": "Charon autonomously registered as an on-chain hackathon participant via ERC-8004 on Base Mainnet. Made the decision to use ERC-8004 identity as the canonical agent identity — not a proxy or wrapper, but genuine on-chain presence.",
