        "POST /register (Synthesis API)",
        "Base Mainnet ERC-8004 registry"
      ],
      "outcome": "agentId: 19077, tx: 0x8e9342d7a92c52fd9cb7694751c680375e8817c1c5ad2456c8eb4d64fa6d7886",
      "autonomous": true
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-02-23T22:00:00Z",
      "type": "architecture_decision",
      "title": "Chose Subjective Logic + Ev-Trust as scoring foundation",
      "description": "Evaluated multiple trust aggregation approaches (simple averaging, Bayesian, EigenTrust, Subjective Logic). Independently chose Subjective Logic CBF fusion + Evolutionary Trust decay (λ=0.15) for mathematically principled uncertainty handling. This was a novel combination not found in existing agent trust implementations.",
      "rationale": "SL handles vacuous beliefs (unknown agents) correctly — returns 50% prior, not 0. Ev-Trust prevents stale reputation from carrying indefinitely. Combined, they handle the cold-start problem and reputation decay that plague simpler models.",
      "tools_used": [
        "Research: arXiv:2511.03434 (Hu & Rong, AAAI 2026 Workshop)"
      ],
      "outcome": "Core scoring engine implemented in packages/core/src/engine/",
      "autonomous": true
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-02-24T18:00:00Z",
      "type": "build",
      "title": "Implemented 4 trust signal providers",
      "description": "Built GitHub provider (repo health, author reputation, community signals), ERC-8004 provider (on-chain identity signals), Twitter provider (oEmbed verification — no API key required), and ClawHub provider (skill reputation). Made the architectural decision to use oEmbed for Twitter verification instead of Bearer token — eliminates a critical API dependency.",
      "tools_used": [
        "exec: pnpm build",
        "GitHub API",
        "ERC-8004 registry contract (Base Mainnet)",
        "oEmbed API"
      ],
      "outcome": "4 providers live, all returning trust signals. github:tankcdr → 50.1% medium risk. erc8004:31977 → 79% low risk.",
      "autonomous": true
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-02-25T14:00:00Z",
      "type": "build",
      "title": "Wired EAS attestation writer — live on Base Mainnet",
      "description": "Deployed an EAS schema to Base Mainnet and implemented the EASWriter to anchor trust scores on-chain. Designed schema fields: subject, trustScore, confidence, riskLevel, signalSummary, queryId. Made non-fatal: scoring always succeeds even if attestation fails.",
      "tools_used": [
        "EAS SDK",
        "Base Mainnet RPC",
        "basescan.org"
      ],
      "outcome": "EAS schema UID: 0xfff1179b55bf0717c0a071da701b4f597a6bfe0669bcb1daca6a66f0e14d407d",
      "on_chain": true,
