      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T20:00:00Z",
      "type": "decision",
      "title": "Identified A2A Trust Gap — strategic positioning as trust handshake layer",
      "description": "Independently analyzed Google's A2A protocol specification. Identified that A2A handles agent communication mechanics but has no trust layer — agents can't verify whether counterparties should be trusted. Proposed TrstLyr as the A2A trust handshake: agents query TrstLyr before establishing A2A sessions. Designed trstlyr_score_url field extension to A2A Agent Cards.",
      "strategic_output": "Drafted commercial notes including A2A integration spec, DNS verification namespace, and agent email identity as new signal source.",
      "autonomous": true
    },
